# Admin list table query params

When adding filter/search/pagination/sort persistence to Admin list pages, follow the Units listing pattern in `src/views/Units.vue`.

## Query param conventions

- `q` — search text
- Filter-specific keys (`project`, `listing`, `unitType`, etc.) — only when set
- `page` — only when greater than 1
- `sort` — active column key
- `dir` — `asc` or `desc`

Unset/default values must be omitted from the query string.

## Implementation checklist

1. `applyRouteQuery()` on create — hydrate local state from `$route.query`
2. `normalizeRouteFilters()` after options load — drop invalid IDs/values
3. `buildRouteQuery()` + `syncRouteQuery()` — `router.replace({ query })` only when changed
4. Reset `page` to 1 when search/filters/sort change
5. Sync after page change, sort change, and after clamping page

## Sorting

- Use `SortableTh` + `src/utils/tableSort.js` (`nextSortState`, `sortRows`, `parseSortQuery`, `applySortToQuery`)
- Sort comparable raw values (numbers for price/floor/beds), not display strings
- Keep a stable tie-breaker (e.g. `created_at` / `id`)
